The paper deals with the encoding complexity of network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the solvability and construction of solutions, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the required number of encoding links and field size, which are topics related to coding theory (cs.CC).
